Reasoning: We inspected the workbook. Columns CB (80) contains a formula that extracts the N‑th largest score from column T (the “Triple Score” column). Column CC (81) currently holds an ArrayFormula object, which is not the desired line‑number (original row index) for each score shown in CB. The instruction says CC should “only display line numbers for the scores that are presented in Column CB”. Therefore we need to replace the ArrayFormula in column CC with a formula that, for each row, finds the position (row number) of the score from CB within the original Triple Score list (column T). The appropriate LibreOffice‑compatible formula is:

    =IFERROR(MATCH(CB2, $T$2:$T$600, 0), "")

This returns the relative position (1‑based) of the score in the range T2:T600, or blank if not found. We will write this formula into every cell of column CC (column 81) from row 2 down to the last row that contains data in column CB. We will leave column CD untouched (the instruction for CD was truncated). After writing the formulas we will save the workbook to the output path, call `recalculate()`, reload with `data_only=True` to verify that the CC cells now contain numeric values (or at least the formula). Finally we will submit the output spreadsheet.
Code:
